OL,3,CBoss 'fully accepts' Gloucestershire
OL,4,Cfire service was 'institutionally
OL,5,Cracist'
OL,7,F"As we grapple with this legacy, I
OL,8,Fmust stress that in accepting the
OL,9,Freport and its findings I am not
OL,10,Fsuggesting in any way that all past or
OL,11,Fserving firefighters and staff were or
OL,12,Fare racist but nor am I saying that
OL,13,Fracism, misogyny and bullying have
OL,14,Fbeen eradicated. There is still work
OL,15,Fto be done."
OL,17,FMr Preece also said he had been to see
OL,18,Fthe family of former workers John
OL,19,FJames and Avanos Biney, who spoke out
OL,20,Fabout their experiences while working
OL,21,Fat the fire service.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/13
